  "name": "RPlog_Homeward_Bound",
  "title": "Rescue and Truce on Dathomir",
  "summary": "Fifteen days after a crash strands Republic and Imperial survivors on a wintering stretch of Dathomir, the two camps have banded together for survival under the loose command of the Marine officers Wrista and Vengan, the pilot Raxis, and the Imperial Marshal Krieg. When a jury-rigged sensor sweep paints fifteen approaching contacts in orbit, the Republic technicians fire up their boosted beacon and raise the NRMF Redemption, which dispatches the Marauder Audacity and a flight of Mercy shuttles under Commander Jared Starwind, escorted by Kyrin Sh'vani's Ghost Squadron. Despite the Marines quietly entrenching for a worst case, Wrista and Raxis negotiate a peaceful, honorable departure with Krieg, leaving the forty-two Imperials a week's supplies and a promise to take no prisoners. The evacuation proceeds without bloodshed; the Republic survivors load aboard while Krieg holds his troops in check, and the relief flight learns of yet another stranded camp fifty clicks south to rescue next.",
